---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title={`Haven Support — Katafract`}
  description={`FAQ and support for Haven DNS — setup, troubleshooting, and common questions.`}
  section="support"
>
  <link slot="head" rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" />
  <style slot="head" is:global set:html={`
    .faq-section { margin: 2rem 0; }
    .faq-item {
      background: var(--bg2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 0.75rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .faq-question {
      padding: 1.25rem;
      background: var(--bg2);
      cursor: pointer;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text);
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      transition: background 0.2s;
    }
    .faq-question:hover {
      background: var(--bg3);
    }
    .faq-toggle {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--dim2);
      font-weight: 400;
    }
    .faq-answer {
      max-height: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
      padding: 0 1.25rem;
    }
    .faq-answer.open {
      max-height: 500px;
      padding: 1.25rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .faq-answer p {
      margin: 0.5rem 0;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--dim);
      line-height: 1.65;
    }
    .faq-answer p:first-child {
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    .faq-answer p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    .faq-answer a {
      color: #4ADE80;
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  `}></style>
  <script slot="head" is:inline set:html={`
    function toggleFaq(id) {
      const answer = document.getElementById(id);
      answer.classList.toggle('open');
    }
  `}></script>
  <Fragment set:html={`<main class="prose-page">
    <div class="prose-header">
      <p class="prose-eyebrow">Haven DNS</p>
      <h1>Support & FAQ</h1>
      <p class="prose-meta">Common questions about installation, troubleshooting, and usage</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-body">

      <div class="faq-section">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq('q1')">
            <span>How do I install Haven on iOS?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle" id="q1-toggle">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="q1">
            <p>Visit <a href="/dns">our DNS setup page</a> on your iPhone using Safari. Tap the link to download the Haven profile. When prompted, open Settings, go to <strong>General → VPN &amp; Device Management</strong>, select the Haven profile, and tap <strong>Install</strong>. Enter your passcode and confirm.</p>
            <p>Once installed, Haven is active system-wide. You can verify it's working by visiting any website and noticing that ads are gone.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq('q2')">
            <span>How do I install Haven on Mac?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle" id="q2-toggle">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="q2">
            <p>Mac supports the same configuration profile as iOS. Download the Haven profile from <a href="/dns">our DNS setup page</a> and open it. macOS will prompt you to open System Settings and install the profile.</p>
            <p>Alternatively, you can manually configure DNS-over-HTTPS in <strong>System Settings → Network → [Your Connection] → Details → DNS</strong>. See our setup page for the exact address.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq('q3')">
            <span>Does Haven work with my router?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle" id="q3-toggle">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="q3">
            <p>Yes, but your router must support DNS-over-HTTPS (DoH) or DNS-over-HTTPS (DoT). Most modern routers from Asus, Netgear, TP-Link, Ubiquiti, and MikroTik support encrypted DNS.</p>
            <p>Log into your router's admin panel and look for DNS settings under <strong>Internet</strong> or <strong>WAN</strong>. Enter the Haven DNS endpoint for your protocol. See <a href="/dns">our setup guide</a> for specific router instructions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq('q4')">
            <span>Why does some website break or show errors?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle" id="q4-toggle">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="q4">
            <p>Haven uses community-maintained blocklists that occasionally over-block legitimate websites. This is rare, but it happens.</p>
            <p>If a site doesn't work, you can temporarily disable Haven by going to <strong>Settings → General → VPN &amp; Device Management</strong>, selecting the Haven profile, and tapping <strong>Delete</strong>. To restore it, reinstall the profile from <a href="/dns">our setup page</a>.</p>
            <p>For persistent issues, let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@katafract.com">hello@katafract.com</a> so we can investigate.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq('q5')">
            <span>How do I uninstall Haven?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle" id="q5-toggle">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="q5">
            <p><strong>On iPhone or iPad:</strong> Go to <strong>Settings → General → VPN &amp; Device Management</strong>, select the Haven profile, and tap <strong>Delete Profile</strong>. Enter your passcode when prompted.</p>
            <p><strong>On Mac:</strong> Go to <strong>System Settings → General → VPN &amp; Device Management</strong> (or <strong>Network</strong> if you configured it manually), remove the Haven profile or DNS settings.</p>
            <p><strong>On your router:</strong> Log in, clear the Haven DNS addresses from your WAN or Internet settings, and save.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr style="border:none;border-top:1px solid var(--border);margin:3rem 0;">

      <h2>Still need help?</h2>
      <p>For questions not covered above, reach out to our team:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@katafract.com">hello@katafract.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Support portal:</strong> <a href="https://katafract.com/support">Visit our support page</a></li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </main>`} />
</Base>
